name: GAL1,10p double overexpression vector
description: GAL1,10p double overexpression vector. TEF terminator cloned into pWJ1781 (NruI digest) Amp, LEU2, CEN, Gal1,10 promoter.
notes: The TEF terminator from a KanMX cassette plasmid (pAG36) was amplified and cloned into the NruI cut site adjacent to the GAL1,10 bi-directional promoter. An NruI cut site was included to allow for double overexpression experiments by cloning into either NruI (downstream of GAL10), or HpaI (Downstream of GAL1)

name: GAL1p-rad5-N155d
notes: rad5-R155MDYKDDDDK (ATGGACTACAAAGACGATGACGACAAG) N-terminal truncation of first 155 residues from rad5 with N-terminal FLAG epitope tag cloned downstream of GAL1 promoter. This version is likely functional since SDL interaction with rad51 is still observed. Sequence verified on 2016-08-29 Eric Bryant: Sequence checked from DNA purified on 2017-11-09

name: GAL1p-FLAG-RAD5
notes: RAD5-M1MDYKDDDDK (ATGGACTACAAAGACGATGACGACAAG) RAD5 with N-terminal FLAG epitope tag cloned downstream of GAL1 promoter. This version is likely functional since SDL interaction with rad51 is still observed. Sequence verified on 2016-08-29 Eric Bryant: sequence verified from DNA purified on 2017-11-09

name: GAL1p-RAD5-FLAG
notes: RAD5-stop1170DYKDDDDKstop (TAG3508GACTACAAAGACGATGACGACAAGTAG) RAD5 with C-terminal FLAG epitope tag cloned downstream of GAL1 promoter. Sequence verified 2016-08-29 Eric Bryant: sequence verified from DNA purified on 2017-11-09

name: mRFP1-LacI
notes: HIS3 marker. mRFP1-LacI expressed from HIS3 promoter. YFP was replaced with mRFP1 in ZOO509. HIS3p-mRFP1-LacI verified by sequencing but bad expression (doesn't form focus on LacO array)

name: GAL1p AID* degron vector
notes: pWJ1781 but with AID* degron (auxin -inducible) from 10.1002/yea.2967 cloned in between A and B adaptamers. Hpa1 site on N-term side of AID and Nru1 site on C-term side for cloning. Gal promoter. Sequence verified 08-2016 by Bob. Nru1 blocked by overlapping Me + upstream Nru1 - so plasmid is best for C-terminal tagging using Hpa1 site

name: GAL1p AID* degron vector
notes: pWJ1894 but with AID* degron (auxin -inducible) cloned in between A and B adaptamers. Hpa1 site on N-term side of AID and Nru1 site on C-term side for cloning. No promoter. Sequence verified 08-2016 by Bob. Nru1 blocked by overlapping Me + upstream Nru1 - so plasmid is best for C-terminal tagging using Hpa1 site
